## MARKETING & AUDIENCE ENGAGEMENT (30 KPIs)

### Digital Marketing (10 KPIs)

#### 146. Social Media Engagement Rate
**Description**: Total interactions divided by total impressions
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better (2-5% is good)
**Data Sources**:
- `social_media_posts` table (likes, comments, shares, impressions)
**Calculation**: `(SUM(likes + comments + shares) / SUM(impressions)) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Hourly
**Visualization**: Line Chart, Gauge

#### 147. Website Conversion Rate
**Description**: Percentage of website visitors who completed desired action
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better
**Data Sources**:
- Web analytics integration
**Calculation**: `(Conversions / Total Visitors) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Hourly
**Visualization**: Gauge, Funnel Chart

#### 148. Landing Page Bounce Rate
**Description**: Percentage of single-page sessions
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Lower is better
**Data Sources**:
- Web analytics integration
**Calculation**: `(Single Page Sessions / Total Sessions) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Hourly
**Visualization**: Gauge

#### 149. Email Campaign Click-Through Rate
**Description**: Percentage of email recipients who clicked links
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better (2-5% is average)
**Data Sources**:
- `email_campaigns` table (emails_clicked, emails_delivered)
**Calculation**: `(SUM(emails_clicked) / SUM(emails_delivered)) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Hourly after send
**Visualization**: Gauge, Bar Chart

#### 150. Email Open Rate
**Description**: Percentage of delivered emails that were opened
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better (15-25% is average)
**Data Sources**:
- `email_campaigns` table (emails_opened, emails_delivered)
**Calculation**: `(SUM(emails_opened) / SUM(emails_delivered)) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Hourly after send
**Visualization**: Gauge, Line Chart

#### 151. Email List Growth Rate
**Description**: Net new subscribers as percentage of total list
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Positive growth
**Data Sources**:
- Email marketing platform integration
**Calculation**: `((New Subscribers - Unsubscribes) / Total Subscribers) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Line Chart

#### 152. Social Media Follower Growth
**Description**: Net new followers gained in period
**Unit**: Count or Percentage
**Target Direction**: Positive growth
**Data Sources**:
- Social media platform API integration
**Calculation**: `(New Followers - Unfollows) / Previous Total × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Line Chart

#### 153. Paid Ad ROAS (Return on Ad Spend)
**Description**: Revenue generated per dollar spent on paid advertising
**Unit**: Ratio (x times)
**Target Direction**: Higher is better (3x+ is good)
**Data Sources**:
- `marketing_campaigns` table (actual_spend, actual_revenue)
**Calculation**: `Revenue from Ads / Ad Spend`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Number, Line Chart

#### 154. Organic Search Traffic Percentage
**Description**: Percentage of website traffic from organic search
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better
**Data Sources**:
- Web analytics integration
**Calculation**: `(Organic Traffic / Total Traffic) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Pie Chart, Line Chart

#### 155. Video View Completion Rate
**Description**: Percentage of video viewers who watched to end
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better
**Data Sources**:
- Video platform analytics integration
**Calculation**: `(Completed Views / Total Views) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Gauge

### Audience Insights (10 KPIs)

#### 156. Net Promoter Score (NPS)
**Description**: Likelihood of attendees recommending event (promoters - detractors)
**Unit**: Score (-100 to +100)
**Target Direction**: Higher is better (50+ is excellent)
**Data Sources**:
- `survey_responses` table (WHERE survey_type = 'nps')
**Calculation**: `(% Promoters [9-10] - % Detractors [0-6])`
**Update Frequency**: Daily after event
**Visualization**: Gauge, Distribution Chart

#### 157. Brand Mention Velocity
**Description**: Number of brand mentions per day during campaign period
**Unit**: Mentions/day
**Target Direction**: Higher is better
**Data Sources**:
- `brand_mentions` table (mentioned_at)
**Calculation**: `COUNT(mentions) / Days in Period`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Line Chart

#### 158. Audience Demographics Match
**Description**: Percentage alignment between target and actual demographics
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better
**Data Sources**:
- `tickets` table (purchaser demographics)
- Target audience profile
**Calculation**: Demographic overlap calculation
**Update Frequency**: Weekly
**Visualization**: Comparison Chart

#### 159. Geographic Reach Diversity
**Description**: Number of different regions/countries represented
**Unit**: Count
**Target Direction**: Higher is better (for growth)
**Data Sources**:
- `tickets` table (billing_city, billing_state, billing_country)
**Calculation**: `COUNT(DISTINCT geographic_units)`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Map, Number

#### 160. Age Distribution Index
**Description**: Breakdown of attendees by age group
**Unit**: Percentage per age group
**Target Direction**: Align with target
**Data Sources**:
- `users` table or ticket purchaser data (age/DOB)
**Calculation**: `COUNT per age group / Total × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Weekly
**Visualization**: Bar Chart, Pie Chart

#### 161. Gender Distribution
**Description**: Gender breakdown of attendees
**Unit**: Percentage per gender
**Target Direction**: Informational
**Data Sources**:
- `users` table or survey data
**Calculation**: `COUNT per gender / Total × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Weekly
**Visualization**: Pie Chart

#### 162. Income Bracket Distribution
**Description**: Economic demographics of attendees
**Unit**: Percentage per bracket
**Target Direction**: Align with target market
**Data Sources**:
- Survey data or inferred from postal codes
**Calculation**: `COUNT per bracket / Total × 100`
**Update Frequency**: After event
**Visualization**: Bar Chart

#### 163. Interest Affinity Score
**Description**: Alignment between event type and attendee interests
**Unit**: Score 0-100
**Target Direction**: Higher is better
**Data Sources**:
- `users` table (interests metadata)
- Event category
**Calculation**: Interest matching algorithm
**Update Frequency**: Weekly
**Visualization**: Number

#### 164. Event Discovery Method
**Description**: How attendees found out about the event
**Unit**: Percentage per channel
**Target Direction**: Informational (guides marketing)
**Data Sources**:
- Survey question or ticket metadata (referral source)
**Calculation**: `COUNT per channel / Total × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Pie Chart, Bar Chart

#### 165. First-Time vs Repeat Ratio
**Description**: Proportion of new attendees to returning attendees
**Unit**: Ratio
**Target Direction**: Balanced (context-dependent)
**Data Sources**:
- `tickets` table (purchaser_id historical lookup)
**Calculation**: `New Attendees : Repeat Attendees`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Ratio display, Pie Chart

### Brand & Experience (10 KPIs)

#### 166. Brand Awareness Lift
**Description**: Increase in brand recognition post-event vs pre-event
**Unit**: Percentage points
**Target Direction**: Positive increase
**Data Sources**:
- Pre and post-event surveys
**Calculation**: `Post-Event Awareness % - Pre-Event Awareness %`
**Update Frequency**: After event
**Visualization**: Comparison Bar

#### 167. Brand Sentiment Score
**Description**: Ratio of positive to total brand mentions
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better (70%+ is good)
**Data Sources**:
- `brand_mentions` table (sentiment)
**Calculation**: `(Positive Mentions / Total Mentions) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Gauge, Line Chart

#### 168. User-Generated Content Volume
**Description**: Number of fan-created posts, photos, videos about event
**Unit**: Count
**Target Direction**: Higher is better
**Data Sources**:
- Social listening integration
- `brand_mentions` table
**Calculation**: `COUNT(user_generated_content)`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Number, Line Chart

#### 169. Hashtag Performance
**Description**: Unique uses of official event hashtag
**Unit**: Count
**Target Direction**: Higher is better
**Data Sources**:
- Social media API integration
**Calculation**: `COUNT(DISTINCT hashtag uses)`
**Update Frequency**: Hourly during event
**Visualization**: Number, Trend Line

#### 170. Media Impressions
**Description**: Total reach through PR and media coverage
**Unit**: Count (impressions)
**Target Direction**: Higher is better
**Data Sources**:
- Media monitoring integration
**Calculation**: `SUM(article reach + broadcast viewers)`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Number, Bar Chart

#### 171. Press Mention Sentiment
**Description**: Percentage of positive press coverage
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better
**Data Sources**:
- Media monitoring integration
**Calculation**: `(Positive Articles / Total Articles) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Gauge

#### 172. Partnership Brand Lift
**Description**: Increase in sponsor/partner brand awareness from event association
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better
**Data Sources**:
- Sponsor survey data
**Calculation**: Post-event awareness increase for sponsors
**Update Frequency**: After event
**Visualization**: Bar Chart

#### 173. Event FOMO Factor
**Description**: Indicator of demand exceeding supply (waitlist + social indicators)
**Unit**: Composite score
**Target Direction**: Higher indicates strong demand
**Data Sources**:
- Waitlist size
- `social_media_posts` table (mentions of sold out)
- `brand_mentions` table (FOMO keywords)
**Calculation**: Composite of multiple demand indicators
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Number

#### 174. Post-Event Engagement Duration
**Description**: Days of continued social engagement after event
**Unit**: Days
**Target Direction**: Longer is better
**Data Sources**:
- `social_media_posts` table (post_date after event)
- `brand_mentions` table (mentioned_at after event)
**Calculation**: Days until engagement drops below threshold
**Update Frequency**: Weekly after event
**Visualization**: Number

#### 175. Content Virality Coefficient
**Description**: Average shares per original post
**Unit**: Ratio
**Target Direction**: Higher is better (>1 is viral)
**Data Sources**:
- `social_media_posts` table (shares per post)
**Calculation**: `AVG(shares / original posts)`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Number, Line Chart

