### Customer Service (10 KPIs)

#### 191. Support Ticket Resolution Time
**Description**: Average hours to resolve customer support tickets
**Unit**: Hours
**Target Direction**: Lower is better (< 24hrs is good)
**Data Sources**:
- Support system integration or
- `communications` table (created_at, resolution timestamp)
**Calculation**: `AVG(resolved_at - created_at) in hours`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Number, Line Chart

#### 192. First Contact Resolution Rate
**Description**: Percentage of issues resolved on first contact
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better (70%+ is good)
**Data Sources**:
- `communications` table (resolution without follow-ups)
**Calculation**: `(First Contact Resolutions / Total Tickets) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Gauge

#### 193. Customer Complaint Rate
**Description**: Number of complaints per 100 attendees
**Unit**: Rate per 100 attendees
**Target Direction**: Lower is better
**Data Sources**:
- `communications` table (complaint flagged)
- `incidents` table
**Calculation**: `(COUNT(complaints) / Total Attendees) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily during and after event
**Visualization**: Number

#### 194. Refund Request Rate
**Description**: Percentage of tickets with refund requests
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Lower is better
**Data Sources**:
- `tickets` table (ticket_status = 'refunded' or refund_amount > 0)
**Calculation**: `(Refund Requests / Total Tickets Sold) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Gauge

#### 195. Support Satisfaction Score
**Description**: Average rating of customer service interactions
**Unit**: Score (1-10 scale)
**Target Direction**: Higher is better (8+ is excellent)
**Data Sources**:
- Post-interaction surveys
**Calculation**: `AVG(support_rating)`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Number

#### 196. Live Chat Response Time
**Description**: Average seconds to first response in live chat
**Unit**: Seconds
**Target Direction**: Lower is better (< 60s is excellent)
**Data Sources**:
- Chat system integration
**Calculation**: `AVG(first_response_time - message_received_time)`
**Update Frequency**: Real-time
**Visualization**: Number

#### 197. Self-Service Success Rate
**Description**: Percentage of customers who resolved issues via self-service
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better
**Data Sources**:
- Help center analytics
- Support ticket deflection data
**Calculation**: `(Self-Resolved / Total Inquiries) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Gauge

#### 198. Escalation Rate
**Description**: Percentage of support tickets that required escalation
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Lower is better
**Data Sources**:
- `communications` table (escalation flag)
**Calculation**: `(Escalated Tickets / Total Tickets) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Gauge

#### 199. Follow-Up Completion Rate
**Description**: Percentage of required follow-ups that were completed
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: 100%
**Data Sources**:
- `communications` table (follow-up required/completed)
**Calculation**: `(Completed Follow-ups / Required Follow-ups) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Daily
**Visualization**: Gauge

#### 200. Service Recovery Success Rate
**Description**: Percentage of complainants satisfied after complaint resolution
**Unit**: Percentage
**Target Direction**: Higher is better (80%+ is good)
**Data Sources**:
- Post-resolution surveys
**Calculation**: `(Satisfied after Resolution / Total Complaints) × 100`
**Update Frequency**: Weekly
**Visualization**: Gauge

